06216nam a22008055i 9783035620801DE-B159720210526051534.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210526t20212021sz     fo  d z      eng d  a2020943214  a97830356208017 a10.1515/97830356208012doi  a(DE-B1597)537207  a(OCoLC)1243312129  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH 7aARC0130002bisacsh0485pa515.2qDE-1011 aZafiris, Elias, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aNatural Communication :bThe Obstacle-Embracing Art of Abstract Gnomonics /cElias Zafiris; ed. by Ludger Hovestadt, Vera Bühlmann. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2021] 4c©2021  a1 online resource (544 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aApplied Virtuality Book Series ;v1400tFrontmatter -- tTABLE OF CONTENTS -- tPROLOGUE -- t1. CIRCULATION: ENCODING-PARTITIONING-DECODING -- t2. TRANSCENDENTAL CIRCULATION: EXPONENTIATION AND LOGARITHMIZATION -- t3. TEMPORAL BONDS: TRIPODAL SPECTRAL ARCHITECTONIC SYNTAXIS OF TIME -- t4. UNDECIDABILITY-UNCERTAINTY: INDIRECT LOGICAL CYCLES AND COMPUTATION -- t5. CIRCUMVENTING COMPLEXITY: MOTIF OF INFORMATION AS ANADYOMENE -- t6. GEOMETRIC CALCULUS: DIFFERENTIAL FORMS AND INTEGRATION -- t7. CANONICS OF INVARIANCE: THE COUPLING OF MATTER WITH FIELDS -- t8. ADJUNCTIONS: CATEGORY THEORY VIA NATURAL COMMUNICATION -- t9. CANONICS OF FUNCTORIAL RELATIONS: SIEVES AND REPRESENTABILITY -- t10. COMMUNICATION TOPOI: QUALIFYING THE PHYSICAL "CONTINUUM" -- t11. FUNCTORIAL GNOMONICS: TEMPORAL PERCOLATION AND ALETHEIA -- tREFERENCES0 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aIn Natural Communication kritisiert der Autor das derzeitige Paradigma der Komplexitätswissenschaften, die Ziele immer spezifisch in den Blick nimmt. Er schlägt eine Alternative vor, die eine grundlegende Architektur der Kommunikation vorstellt. Sein Modell der "natürlichen Kommunikation" schließt moderne theoretische Konzepte aus Mathematik und Physik mit ein, insbesondere der Kategorietheorie und der Quantenmechanik. Er abstrahiert daraus präzise Grundbegriffe, die zu einer terminologischen Basis dieser Theorie führen und die Möglichkeit eröffnen, mit Komplexität neu umzugehen. Der Autor ist davon überzeugt, dass es nur durch einen Blick in die Vergangenheit möglich ist, eine Kontinuität und Kohärenz in unserer gegenwärtigen Denkweise herzustellen, insbesondere in Bezug auf die Komplexität.  aIn Natural Communication, the author criticizes the current paradigm of specific goal orientation in the complexity sciences and proposes an alternative that envisions a fundamental architectonics of communication. His model of "natural communication" encapsulates modern theoretical concepts from mathematics and physics, in particular category theory and quantum theory. From these fields it abstracts precise concepts such as to constitute a terminological basis for this theory which offers the opportunity to open up novel ways of thinking about complexity. The author is convinced that it is only possible to establish a continuity and coherence with contemporary thinking, especially with respect to complexity, through looking into the past.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 4aAdjunction. 4aConjugation. 4aCovering. 4aSheaves. 4aStructural Complexity. 4aTopoi. 7aARCHITECTURE / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh1 aBühlmann, Vera, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHovestadt, Ludger, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2021z978311075070608iTi